'''Janner''' refers to any english person born within 10 miles of the sea. However, it has come somewhat of a derogatory term and many use it to describe the lower classes from the city of [[Plymouth]] in south-west [[Devon]].  The term is used with the same meaning as [[chav]] by some students in Plymouth. For example: "I dont want to go down Union Street, it is full of janners."

Well, being a Janner myself I don`t take kindly to hearing the term allegedly becoming a derogatory term by "many", where "many" seems to equate to students (of which I used to be one).  I for one have never heard it used this way and would pull anyone up on it should they do so; it being extremely rascist.